&lt;p&gt;Static Care of the Elderly Rehabilitation Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Winter pressure - 37.5 Hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary (pro rata) £24,214 – £30,112&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and well-motivated to join us in the Physiotherapy Department at Clifton Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, well-motivated and skilled Physiotherapist to join us in the Therapy department at Clifton Hospital which is part of Blackpool Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. A vacancy has arisen for a Band 5 Physiotherapy with the Rehabilitation service. You must have previous clinical experience within Rehabilitation and demonstrate an enthusiastic, forward thinking and problem solving approach to patient assessment management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Band 6 clinician you will be required to take part in helping to deliver a quality Physiotherapy 7-day service, assisting the Clinical Lead to develop new ways of working in order to deliver timely and appropriate care to patients. The hours will be spread over 7 days. You must have excellent communication and interpersonal skills, demonstrating the ability to support junior staff and Technical Instructors within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the post holder you will be responsible for the provision of Physiotherapy triage, assessment, intervention and discharge planning of patients with multiple and often complex diagnoses. You will also work with other members of the multi-disciplinary team in order to provide a patient-centred service working to identify patient needs, ensuring a safe and timely discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to undergraduate education, CPD, clinical governance and flexible working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
